      "writtenOn": "2021-04-21T14:55:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Parameters (i.e. layout keys, \"SectionAndParameterHelper::IsParameter\" \u003d\u003d true) are a total special case and don\u0027t use getDSLModifiers at all. See DSLCPPCodeGenerator.cpp:818.\n\nFor parameters, I experimented with multiple approaches before landing on this one. My first attempt was this:\n\n    auto colorWhite \u003d Half4(_outer.rR,_outer.rG,_outer.rB,_outer.rA);\n\nHowever, this totally doesn\u0027t work at all. `colorWhite` is a loose DSLExpression. DSL wasn\u0027t really built with a free-floating DSLExpression in mind. You can\u0027t copy it or clone it. You can std::move it and use it exactly one time. :( This was pretty much a non-starter.\n\nI also experimented with\n\n    #define colorWhite Half4(_outer.rR,_outer.rG,_outer.rB,_outer.rA)\n\nThis actually did pretty much work! OTOH, it felt gross compared to declaring a const variable and letting constant-propagation do its thing. We can experiment with this more if you\u0027re interested though.",
